00:00:01.070 --> 00:00:03.000
&gt;&gt; From the Library of
Congress in Washington, D.C.

00:00:18.060 --> 00:00:19.360
&gt;&gt; Nancy Groce: Hello.

00:00:19.360 --> 00:00:20.660
My name is Nancy Groce.

00:00:20.660 --> 00:00:24.300
I'm a folklorist at the American
Folklife Center here at the Library

00:00:24.300 --> 00:00:27.950 position:56%
of Congress, and I'd like to welcome
you to the latest presentation

00:00:27.950 --> 00:00:31.960
on our ongoing Benjamin
A. Botkin Lecture Series.

00:00:31.960 --> 00:00:34.980
The Botkin Series allows
us to highlight the work

00:00:34.980 --> 00:00:37.300
of leading scholars in the
discipline of folklore,

00:00:37.300 --> 00:00:39.320
ethnomusicology, oral history

00:00:39.320 --> 00:00:42.230
and cultural heritage while
enhancing the collections here

00:00:42.230 --> 00:00:44.110
at the American Folklife Center.

00:00:44.110 --> 00:00:46.370
