00:28:35.590 --> 00:28:37.350
by peasant foresting.

00:28:37.350 --> 00:28:41.050
This mushroom's life ways are
complex, always a-tuned to

00:28:41.050 --> 00:28:44.650
and responding to other factors
in its immediate environment.

00:28:44.650 --> 00:28:48.490
Matsutake's [inaudible] is out
of step with modern capitalism,

00:28:48.490 --> 00:28:52.490
which is predicated on the ability
to scale up, to expand smoothly

00:28:52.490 --> 00:28:56.090
in new spaces without having to
rethink its framing assumptions.

00:28:56.090 --> 00:29:02.330
Scalability is achieved, she
writes, by minimizing encounter.

00:29:02.330 --> 00:29:07.010 position:56%
Monoculture plantations, for
instance, become infinitely scalable

00:29:07.010 --> 00:29:11.460
by first wiping local context
clean by clear cutting forests,

00:29:11.460 --> 00:29:13.280
concreting existing communities

00:29:13.280 --> 00:29:15.930
and then importing cologne
[phonetic] sugar cane sort

00:29:15.930 --> 00:29:20.270
of a plant life that's
oblivious to encounter

00:29:20.270 --> 00:29:23.560
and coerced labor that's been
shorn of social relations

00:29:23.560 --> 00:29:25.560 position:56%
that could make a difference, right?

00:29:25.560 --> 00:29:27.910
This plantation style alienation

00:29:27.910 --> 00:29:30.530
where parts are infinitely
interchangeable and exchangeable

00:29:30.530 --> 00:29:33.800
in the market can also been
seen in fast food franchises,

00:29:33.800 --> 00:29:37.570
which seem so similar and
the workers so dispensable.

00:29:37.570 --> 00:29:41.050
Blank slate ferments in the
food world are another example

00:29:41.050 --> 00:29:44.970
of an attempt to make production
predictable by mitigating context.

00:29:44.970 --> 00:29:48.510 position:56%
In this case, makers of cheese, beer
or wine produce a consistent product

00:29:48.510 --> 00:29:51.900
by first removing existing
organisms in the base liquid

00:29:51.900 --> 00:29:55.070
and then re-inoculating
it with a pure culture

00:29:55.070 --> 00:30:00.040
of the bacteria they
wish to do its work.

00:30:00.040 --> 00:30:01.750
So I've been thinking about
scalability in relation to the ways

00:30:01.750 --> 00:30:03.410
that home canning is
often coupled narratively

00:30:03.410 --> 00:30:05.240
to fear and to compliance.

00:30:05.240 --> 00:30:08.400
If you Google botulism, you
get pictures of Mason jars.

00:30:08.400 --> 00:30:11.240
